doc.previous: Newton metres and joules are dimensionally equivalent in the sense that they have the same expression in SI base units
doc.after: Again N m and J are distinguished in order to avoid misunderstandings where a torque is mistaken for an energy or vice versa Similar examples of dimensionally equivalent units include Pa versus J m Bq versus Hz and ohms versus ohms per square
